quran[11]{c,v,t,f}:
  17,76,"They almost provoked you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>so as to evict you from the land, and in that case they would not have lasted after you except briefly;"
  17,77,"such has been Our rule with the messengers We have sent before you, and you never find any change in Our rule."
  17,78,"Establish<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>the prayer at the decline of the sun until the dusk of the night, as well as the Recitation{1}at dawn; indeed, Recitation at dawn has always been witnessed.",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is Qur’anwhich literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.
  17,79,"And keep vigil with it during parts of the night as an extra<i class=""s"">(deed) </i>; hopefully your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord will raise you to a laudable position."
  17,80,"And say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “My Lord, let me enter through an entry of truth and let me exit through an exit of truth and grant me from You a supporting manifestation.”"
  17,81,"And say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “Truth has come while falsehood has withered away; indeed, falsehood is bound to wither away.”"
  17,82,"And We <span class=""h"">bestow from on high<sup foot_note=""80453"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>of the Recital<a class=""sup""><sup>d </sup></a>that which is a healing and a mercy for the believers, but it does not increase the unjust except in loss."
  17,83,"And when We bless man, he disregards<i class=""s"">(Us) </i>and <span class=""h"">distances himself<sup foot_note=""80454"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>. But when evil touches him, he staunchly despairs."
  17,84,"Say, “Each does according to his disposition, but your<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>Lord knows better of the one who is more guided to the way.”"
  17,85,"And they ask you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>about the Spirit; say, “The Spirit is by the command of my Lord, and you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>were not given of knowledge but little.”"
  17,86,"And if We will, we can surely take away what We have revealed to you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, then you would find for yourself no trustee against Us—"
